This paper deals with event detection in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves keyword-based matching and information retrieval, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
